content.text:
The issue was that `CardTemplatePreviewer` was not using the `ordinal` passed from the Note Editor to set the initial card index. Instead, it was defaulting to `cardIndex = 0`. This caused the preview to always show the first card (or an empty card) instead of the selected card.

I fixed this by:
1.  Modifying `onCollectionLoaded` in `CardTemplatePreviewer.kt` to calculate the correct `cardIndex` based on `mOrdinal`.
2.  Implementing logic to handle Cloze cards correctly, where `mOrdinal` (0-based) needs to be mapped to the correct card index using `clozeNumbersInNote` (which returns 1-based cloze numbers).
3.  Adding an optimization to skip this calculation if `mOrdinal` is 0 (since `cardIndex` defaults to 0), which also avoids potential side effects in existing tests.

I verified the fix by creating a reproduction test case `CardTemplatePreviewerReproduceTest.kt` which confirmed the bug and then the fix. I also ran existing tests to ensure no regressions.

The fix ensures that when a user selects a specific card (e.g., c3) in the browser and previews it in the Note Editor, the correct card is displayed.

I deleted the temporary reproduction test file before submitting.

